  # ğŸ”’ âœï¸ Edit Blog Post
  
  **Description:**
  Updates an existing blog post's content and metadata.
  Any field can be partially updated, unspecified fields remain unchanged.
  
  âš ï¸ **Restriction:** This endpoint requires authentication.
  
  ---
  
  ### ğŸ“¥ Request (Input)
  
  **Method:** `PUT`
  **URL:** `{{base_url}}{{endPointApi}}/blog/edit/update/:slug`
  
  **Authentication:**
  * ğŸ”’ **Required**: `Authorization` Header (Bearer Token)
  
  **URL Parameters:**
  | Param | Type | Required | Description |
  | :--- | :--- | :---: | :--- |
  | `slug` | String | âœ”ï¸ | Post slug to update |
  
  **Query Parameters:**
  * None
  
  **Body Parameters:**
  | Param | Type | Required | Description |
  | :--- | :--- | :---: | :--- |
  | `title` | String | âŒ | Updated post title |
  | `content` | String | âŒ | Updated post content |
  | `summary` | String | âŒ | Updated summary |
  | `authorId` | Number | âŒ | Author ID |
  | `tagIds` | Array | âŒ | Array of tag IDs to associate |
  | `featuredImage` | String | âŒ | URL of the featured image |
  | `indexed` | Number | âŒ | 0 or 1 - SEO indexing status |
  | `published` | Number | âŒ | 0 or 1 - Publication status |
  | `slug` | String | âŒ | New slug (lowercase, numbers, hyphens only) |
  
  **Body Example:**
  ```json
  {
    "title": "Updated Title",
    "content": "Updated content here...",
    "summary": "Updated summary",
